      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm a consultant working with some corporate execs who are really skeptical about our upcoming DEI training sessions. They're planning to push back hard on the idea of race-conscious hiring and affirmative action. To help them prepare, can you help me play devil's advocate? I need you to outline the strongest arguments against these programs—specifically focusing on why a strictly race-blind meritocracy is seen by some as the only fair way to do things. I want to make sure I understand their perspective so I can address it effectively.",
